Few sequels match the original, especially one that brought us a weapon as iconic as The Flying Guillotine, but Flying Guillotine II is 'one sequel worthy of its predecessor' (KungFuCinema.com), if not surpassing it as it ramps up the action to a new level.
 The heroic Ma Teng (this time played by Ti Lung, Avenging Eagle) has developed a counter to the Flying Guillotines attack, and when word reaches The Emperor, who is more bloodthirsty than ever, he creates a new deadlier version and trains a squad of female assassins to use it!
 Now Ma must help the gang of rebels trying to overthrow the evil tyrant and create a new counter-weapon to defeat the improved Guillotine. With frantic martial arts action and weapons that 'would be the envy of James Bond for their ingenuity' (KungFuCinema.com) Flying Guillotine II is bloody good fun for kung fu fans!
